name: hvacampr-equipment-environmental-chambers
notes: Description:   Large &quot;Truck&quot; Chamber  The large &quot;truck&quot; chamber provides controlled air conditions from -7 &#176;C (20 &#176;F) to 65 &#176;C (150 &#176;F).  Air-Conditioner and Heat Pump Test Chambers  The indoor chamber can provide controlled air conditions for all ARI heating and cooling tests for split-systems, window units, and other unitary equipment throughout the range of 10 &#176;C (50 &#176;F) to 60 &#176;C (140 &#176;F) dry-bulb temperature with relative humidity controlled within &#177;2 %.   Small Appliance and Refrigerator Chamber  This chamber is used to test small heating and cooling equipment such as radiators, heat exchangers, water coolers, refrigerators, and control devices.  Specifications / Capabilities:   Large &quot;Truck&quot; Chamber  The conditioning equipment can remove up to 35 kW (120 000 Btu/h) of heat at a dry-bulb temperature of 35&#176;C (95&#176;F) and 50 % relative humidity. Full range dry-bulb temperature control of &#177; 1&#176;C (2&#176;F) with relative humidity control better than &#177; 2 % is possible. At ARI heating and cooling conditions, control of dry-bulb and dewpoint temperatures are better than 0.1 &#176;C (0.2 &#176;F).   Air-Conditioner and Heat Pump Test Chambers  The outdoor chamber has a temperature range capability from -18&#176;C (0 &#176;F) to 60 &#176;C (140 &#176;F) with relative humidity controlled within &#177; 2%. At ARI heating and cooling conditions, control of dry-bulb and dewpoint temperatures are better than 0.1&#176;C (0.2&#176;F). Units with cooling capacities up to 35 kW (120 000 Btu/h) may be tested.   Small Appliance and Refrigerator Chamber  Dry-bulb temperature may be controlled from -18&#176;C (0&#176;F) to 65&#176;C (150&#176;F) with relative humidity controlled within &#177; 2% of setpoint. At ARI heating and cooling conditions, control of dry-bulb and dewpoint temperatures are better than 0.1&#176;C (0.2&#176;F). Maximum heat removal from this chamber is 11.7 kW (40 000 Btu/h).
title: HVAC&R Equipment Environmental Chambers
